snippet: The Federal Reserve said manufacturing output declined 0.04 percent in January, but a similar report from the New York Fed indicated the drop-off could be temporary.
abstract: Federal Reserve says that manufacturing output in United States has declined 0.04 percent in January 2013, but similar report from New York Federal Reserve Bank indicates drop-off could be temporary.
